which
told
him
the
hour.
It
was
a
quarter
past
nine.
He
calculated
the
distances,
and
the
short
time
which
it
would
take
him
to
perform
so
trivial
an
operation.
He
ought
to
reach
Lady
Sannox
by
ten
o'clock.
Through
the
fogged
